            <h3 class="subtitle">Deforestation Definition Used</h3>
            <p>GFW’s satellite-based forest monitoring system detects and reports all instances of gross tree cover loss, regardless of whether the loss will be permanent (deforestation) or temporary (loss occurring within managed forests). Thus loss of tree cover in one year does not necessarily lead to a deforestation event.</p>

            <p>Efforts are currently underway by GFW partners to address this issue by identifying drivers of change and subsequent land use. At this time, users are encouraged to filter available tree cover extent and loss data to meet their specific monitoring objective.</p>
